Interface StateArrayContributor<J>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DomainType<J>, DomainTypeDescriptor<J>, ExpressableType<J>, Fetchable<J>, Navigable<J>, Readable, Serializable, Type<J>, Writeable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BagPersistentAttribute<O,E>, IdentifierBagAttribute<O,E>, ListPersistentAttribute<D,E>, MapPersistentAttribute<D,K,V>, NonIdPersistentAttribute<O,J>, PluralPersistentAttribute<O,C,E>, SetPersistentAttribute<D,E>, VersionDescriptor<O,J>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractNonIdSingularPersistentAttribute, AbstractPluralPersistentAttribute

    public interface StateArrayContributor<J>
extends Navigable<J>, ExpressableType<J>, Fetchable<J>, Readable
    Optional contract for a Navigable that can be part of it's container's state array.

    • Method Detail

      • getStateArrayPosition

        int getStateArrayPosition()
        Defines this contributor's position within the state array.
        "API Note:"
        Much like PersistentAttributeDescriptor.getAttributePosition(), this position follows a pre-defined algorithm based on alphabetical order, super types first. Note however, that this ordering is only important internally as Hibernate builds the container's "state array" as part of EntityEntry, actions, cache entries, etc

      • resolveHydratedState

        default Object resolveHydratedState(Object hydratedForm,
                                    ExecutionContext executionContext,
                                    SharedSessionContractImplementor session,
                                    Object containerInstance)
        Given a hydrated representation of this Readable, resolve its domain representation.

        E.g. for a composite, the hydrated form is an Object[] representing the "simple state" of the composite's attributes. Resolution of those values returns the instance of the component with its resolved values injected.
